-- Raymond James Hires Barclays’ McOuat for Mining Investment Group
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-06-07T15:19:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-07/raymond-james-hires-barclays-mcouat-for-mining-investment-group.html
Raymond James Ltd., the Canadian
subsidiary of Raymond James Financial Inc., hired Gavin McOuat
from  Barclays Plc (BARC)  to expand its mining investment banking group.  McOuat will be based in Toronto as managing director and
co-head of investment banking mining and metals starting June
10, the firm said today in a statement. He’ll work with  John
Murphy , co-head of mining in Vancouver. McOuat was previously
global co-head of metals and mining for Barclays.  “He has a strong reputation for his ability to identify
and build deep relationships with clients, and is widely
respected throughout the mining industry in North America and
internationally,” Jason Holtby, head of investment banking for
Raymond James, said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
